nice to have if you travel frequently. When you use your card to purchase your travel fare, you automatically qualify for travel accident insurance, rental car insurance and lost luggage reimbursement. Plus, this card includes purchase protection and extended product warranty when you use your card for certain purchases.","There isn&#39;t an introductory annual percentage rate promotion with this air miles card, but its standard APR is relatively low. For the purchases and balance transfers that you make with this card, you can expect a 13.99% to 21.99% (Variable) APR. If you use this card to make a cash advance, you can expect a 25.24% Variable APR, and this card has a 29.99% Variable penalty APR.","For the first year that you have this card, Citi waives the $95 annual fee. The other fees that are associated with this card are industry standard, although not all charge you the 3% international purchase fee that is included on this card, which means that when you travel overseas and use this card, a 3% fee for every transaction is tacked on to each purchase. For cash advances, you pay a minimum $10 or 5% fee, and for balance transfers you pay a minimum $5 or 3% fee per transaction.","You can contact Citi for member support via phone 24 hours a day, 7 days a week. Live chat is also available. The company provides frequently asked questions on its website that you can use to find answers to general questions about your card benefits or account."]},"id":"f709ad4e-3a47-43c5-8302-789dda563d92","type":"text"},{"data":{"text":"Summary"},"id":"5c9d42df-703c-4023-af0a-21147ac32de2","type":"heading"},{"data":{"paragraphs":["The Citi® / AAdvantage® Platinum Select® MasterCard® air miles credit card is an acceptable option if you frequently fly with American Airlines. It provides you with several travel benefits, like the free bag check for you and up to four travel companions, that can make traveling more convenient.","<em>Disclaimer: The Annual Percentage Rate or APR is refle